  <tr>
    <td class="headerbox" style="width:380px"><em>Introducing E-FLO™ Electroporation System</em></td>
    <td style="width:150px;background-color:#FFFFFF;padding:0px"><img src="topimages/featurebox-corner.gif" width="150" height="20" align="left"></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2" valign="top" style="border-right:solid 1px #666666;border-bottom:solid 1px #666666;border-left:solid 1px #666666;padding:10px 10px 10px 20px;font-size:.75em;"><a href="news-product.asp?npid=274"><img src="topimages/feature-E-FLO.jpg" alt="Potato Chips" width="173" height="195" align="right" style="margin:0 15px 5px 12px;"></a>
<div style="margin:7px 0 0 0;"><img src="topimages/bulletpointTOP.gif" width="7" height="10" align="absmiddle" style="margin-right: 4px;"><strong style="color:#222266;font-size:1.10em">New preparation system that will change<br />the way you think about potato processing</strong><br/><div style="margin:18px 0 12px 12px;line-height:16px;">Using Pulse Electric Field Processing (PEF) the patent protected E-FLO Electroporation System provides significant product improvement in chip crunch, taste and texture as well as reduction in acrylamide formation and oil content. The system also replaces or reduces the need to blanch.</div><img src="images/spacer.gif" width="220" height="1" border="0"><a href="news-product.asp?npid=274" class="bluenav" style="font-weight:bold">MORE<img src="topimages/redarrow.gif" width="8" height="8" align="absmiddle" style="margin-left:3px;"></a></div></td>
